This paper deals with online learning and decision making in adversarial environments, which are topics that are commonly studied in the machine learning and artificial intelligence communities. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a new algorithm for solving constrained optimization problems, which falls under the scope of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper analyzes the performance of the proposed algorithm in terms of regret and constraint violation, which is related to the field of cs.GT (Game Theory).
